think it's helping.

549
00:41:33,680 --> 00:41:34,440
I'm seeing...

550
00:41:37,200 --> 00:41:38,240
I'm not seeing clearly.

551
00:41:39,720 --> 00:41:41,920
- Well, it's been tough
on all of us, Bobby.

552
00:41:43,480 --> 00:41:44,360
I lost my daughter.

553
00:41:46,120 --> 00:41:47,080
- I know.

554
00:41:48,480 --> 00:41:49,760
I wish it was me driving.

555
00:41:51,880 --> 00:41:52,640
- I think.

556
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:55,200
I think it's best if we leave.

557
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:58,440
- Yeah, I think that's best.

558
00:41:58,440 --> 00:42:00,120
We don't wanna go
down that road again.

559
00:42:02,560 --> 00:42:05,720
- (chuckles) No.

560
00:42:07,120 --> 00:42:08,720
Why would we want
to relive that?

561
00:42:11,800 --> 00:42:14,360
(door shutting)

562
00:42:30,280 --> 00:42:32,720
(car starting)

563
00:42:37,840 --> 00:42:40,480
(pills rattling)

564
00:42:48,640 --> 00:42:49,400
- Wow.

565
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:52,160
That's...

566
00:42:54,080 --> 00:42:55,360
Pretty sad there, honey.

567
00:42:57,600 --> 00:43:00,240
You couldn't pick up our son
and then you hit the liquor

568
00:43:00,240 --> 00:43:01,880
and the coffee like it's water.

569
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:04,160
She's never gonna let you take--

570
00:43:04,160 --> 00:43:05,760
- Leave me alone!

571
00:43:05,760 --> 00:43:08,560
You're not here anymore, you
have no right to criticize me!

572
00:43:08,560 --> 00:43:10,200
- Oh, so you do feel something?

573
00:43:11,640 --> 00:43:12,400
That's good.

574
00:43:20,680 --> 00:43:22,440
- Please, stop.

575
00:43:22,440 --> 00:43:25,200
Please just stop this.

576
00:43:25,200 --> 00:43:28,240
(forcibly exhales)

577
00:44:16,200 --> 00:44:17,480
- Morning, sunshine.

578
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:19,320
- You're here.

579
00:44:19,320 --> 00:44:20,080
- Yep.

580
00:44:21,240 --> 00:44:22,480
It's cold in here.

581
00:44:22,480 --> 00:44:24,120
- Oh, let me get
you another blanket.

582
00:44:28,840 --> 00:44:29,720
I got this.

583
00:44:29,720 --> 00:44:31,200
I got this, I got this.

584
00:44:31,200 --> 00:44:32,680
- A blanket's not gonna help me.

585
00:44:34,160 --> 00:44:35,560
I need you to listen to me.

586
00:44:36,840 --> 00:44:38,440
I need you to get
your act together.

587
00:44:39,640 --> 00:44:40,920
They're not gonna let
you take care of--

588
00:44:40,920 --> 00:44:42,960
- No, no, no, I got
a blanket right here.

589
00:44:46,000 --> 00:44:47,440
No!

590
00:44:47,440 --> 00:44:48,720
No.

591
00:44:48,720 --> 00:44:50,120
No, I got you a
blanket, don't go.

592
00:45:13,440 --> 00:45:16,600
(taking deep breaths)

593
00:45:47,680 --> 00:45:49,840
(wincing)

594
00:45:57,880 --> 00:45:58,720
Hey, Andrew.

595
00:45:58,720 --> 00:45:59,760
Yeah, it's me, Bobby.

596
00:46:01,960 --> 00:46:04,680
Yeah, I wanted to see if maybe
you wanted to go for a walk,

597
00:46:04,680 --> 00:46:06,000
up in the woods.

598
00:46:08,760 --> 00:46:09,600
Yeah, like a hike.

599
00:46:11,320 --> 00:46:12,880
You know, I'm just...

600
00:46:12,880 --> 00:46:15,520
Just getting a little
stir crazy in here and...

601
00:46:19,120 --> 00:46:20,560
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

602
00:46:20,560 --> 00:46:21,320
Sure.

603
00:46:22,560 --> 00:46:24,760
Uh-huh, yeah, well
another time, then.

604
00:46:25,920 --> 00:46:26,680
Yep.

605
00:46:39,560 --> 00:46:40,320
Bridgette?

606
00:47:06,240 --> 00:47:07,560
- Hey, sunshine.

607
00:47:07,560 --> 00:47:08,320
- Bridgette.

608
00:47:10,080 --> 00:47:10,840
What are you doing?

609
00:47:10,840 --> 00:47:11,760
You look so pale.

610
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:12,520
- I'm fine, I can't feel this.

611
00:47:12,520 --> 00:47:13,520
- But you look so pale.

612
00:47:14,720 --> 00:47:16,000
- Looks can be deceiving.

613
00:47:17,600 --> 00:47:20,600
Bobby, I need you to promise me

614
00:47:20,600 --> 00:47:22,240
you're gonna take
care of our son.

615
00:47:23,440 --> 00:47:25,240
- It's not that easy, I...

616
00:47:25,240 --> 00:47:26,200
I don't know.

617
00:47:26,200 --> 00:47:27,120
I don't know what I'm doing.

618
00:47:27,120 --> 00:47:28,240
- Baby, it doesn't matter.

619
00:47:29,760 --> 00:47:31,960
Please, just promise me you're
not gonna let her do this.

620
00:47:31,960 --> 00:47:33,120
(branch snapping)

621
00:47:33,120 --> 00:47:33,880
- Hello?

622
00:47:39,120 --> 00:47:40,640
Andrew!

623
00:47:40,640 --> 00:47:42,760
What are you doing out here?

624
00:47:42,760 --> 00:47:45,240
- Once I got off the
phone I started thinking,

625
00:47:45,240 --> 00:47:46,480
what am I gonna do at work?

626
00:47:46,480 --> 00:47:47,600
- Wait, work?

627
00:47:48,520 --> 00:47:49,720
What is today?

628
00:47:49,720 --> 00:47:52,560
- It's Tuesday, Bobby.

629
00:47:52,560 --> 00:47:53,840
- Oh.

630
00:47:53,840 --> 00:47:54,760
Sorry, I wouldn't
have called you

631
00:47:54,760 --> 00:47:56,080
if I knew it was a work day.

632
00:47:56,080 --> 00:47:57,280
- Yeah, so I packed
up my bag, you know,

633
00:47:57,280 --> 00:47:59,920
I called my boss, "I'll
see you tomorrow."

634
00:47:59,920 --> 00:48:01,440
Came out here to get
some fresh air with you.

635
00:48:02,560 --> 00:48:03,320
- Oh.

636
00:48:04,640 --> 00:48:05,400
Thanks.

637
00:48:07,720 --> 00:48:08,480
I'm shocked.

638
00:48:11,320 --> 00:48:12,080
Want some rum?

639
00:48:13,520 --> 00:48:15,240
- No, no, not really.

640
00:48:17,400 --> 00:48:18,120
Well, okay.

641
00:48:26,960 --> 00:48:28,280
Hey, were you saying something?

642
00:48:28,280 --> 00:48:30,360
I thought I heard your
voice when I was coming up.

643
00:48:30,360 --> 00:48:32,840
- (scoffs) I've been
talking to myself a lot.

644
00:48:34,200 --> 00:48:35,680
It's quiet at the lake house.

645
00:48:39,600 --> 00:48:40,360
- Bobby.

646
00:48:42,600 --> 00:48:43,440
Are you all right?

647
00:48:58,280 --> 00:48:59,840
- Sometimes I think that I am.

648
00:49:03,240 --> 00:49:04,240
Then this wave hits me,

649
00:49:06,280 --> 00:49:08,480
this tsunami of
uncontrollable sadness

650
00:49:08,480 --> 00:49:10,280
and it just knocks me down.

651
00:49:13,120 --> 00:49:14,320
- I think that's normal.

652
00:49:16,960 --> 00:49:19,560
I think that's how
you're supposed to feel.

653
00:49:19,560 --> 00:49:21,960
- And I can't get my feet
under me or anything.

654
00:49:23,200 --> 00:49:23,960
You know?

655
00:49:31,160 --> 00:49:34,200
I miss her so much.

656
00:49:37,240 --> 00:49:41,920
And I don't think I'm
handling that very well.

657
00:49:45,200 --> 00:49:46,160
I hurt.

658
00:49:48,200 --> 00:49:49,160
All the time and...

659
00:49:52,560 --> 00:49:54,080
Some things numb the pain, but.

660
00:49:56,720 --> 00:49:59,440
I wake up in the morning and
it's still there, you know?

661
00:50:03,520 --> 00:50:06,440
And I want to stop hurting, but
I can't stop hurting myself.

662
00:50:06,440 --> 00:50:08,960
I mean, I can barely
even get into a car.

663
00:50:17,440 --> 00:50:20,240
I try to cry sometimes and
then no tears come out,

664
00:50:20,240 --> 00:50:22,160
because it's like
I have none left.

665
00:50:24,560 --> 00:50:26,200
And I have a son.

666
00:50:30,840 --> 00:50:33,920
And I can't help him,
he can't help me.

667
00:50:35,360 --> 00:50:36,320
I can't be a father.

668
00:50:37,520 --> 00:50:38,840
I mean, I don't know
what I'm supposed to do.

669
00:50:38,840 --> 00:50:40,880
What am I supposed to
do with a child, huh?

670
00:50:40,880 --> 00:50:41,640
Seriously.

671
00:50:45,360 --> 00:50:46,120
- I don't know.

672
00:50:49,200 --> 00:50:50,160
I don't, man.

673
00:50:52,160 --> 00:50:53,080
I won't pretend to.

674
00:51:00,440 --> 00:51:01,200
- Thanks.

675
00:51:03,800 --> 00:51:06,280
Thanks for not pretending
to have all the answers.

676
00:51:17,280 --> 00:51:18,440
- Come on, let me
take you to dinner

677
00:51:18,440 --> 00:51:21,160
at that diner we used
to go to in high school.

678
00:51:21,160 --> 00:51:23,680
- I don't know if
that's a good idea.

679
00:51:23,680 --> 00:51:24,880
- Why not?

680
00:51:24,880 --> 00:51:26,880
- I don't really
wanna get into a car.

681
00:51:26,880 --> 00:51:28,240
I don't really wanna see people.

682
00:51:28,400 --> 00:51:30,880
I don't wanna leave
the woods, the cabin.

683
00:51:32,200 --> 00:51:32,960
It's quiet here.

684
00:51:34,200 --> 00:51:37,200
I'm safe.

685
00:51:37,200 --> 00:51:38,160
- Come on.

686
00:51:39,480 --> 00:51:40,240
Come on.

687
00:51:43,280 --> 00:51:44,240
We're going.

688
00:51:45,760 --> 00:51:48,120
(Bobby sighs)

689
00:52:44,760 --> 00:52:45,920
- How many?
- Two.

690
00:52:49,600 --> 00:52:50,560
- Follow me.

691
00:52:52,080 --> 00:52:53,040
This good?

692
00:52:53,040 --> 00:52:53,800
- Perfect.

693
00:53:18,760 --> 00:53:19,760
Startling, isn't it?

694
00:53:19,760 --> 00:53:20,520
- What?

695
00:53:21,880 --> 00:53:23,480
Did she say something?

696
00:53:23,480 --> 00:53:24,680
- Who?

697
00:53:24,680 --> 00:53:25,720
No, this place.

698
00:53:25,720 --> 00:53:27,160
It's like it doesn't change.

699
00:53:28,160 --> 00:53:29,880
It's like stuck in a time warp.

700
00:53:29,880 --> 00:53:31,280
Even that waitress is the same.

701
00:53:33,120 --> 00:53:33,880
- I think you're right.

702
00:53:38,600 --> 00:53:40,400
Thanks for bringing me here.

703
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:41,680
- Yeah.

704
00:53:41,680 --> 00:53:43,000
Sorry it isn't one of
those bougie restaurants

705
00:53:43,000 --> 00:53:45,640
like you like to go
to in the city, but.

706
00:53:45,640 --> 00:53:47,320
- Oh, that was Bridgette
that liked those.

707
00:53:47,320 --> 00:53:50,080
I was always much
more comfortable in
a place like this.

708
00:53:50,080 --> 00:53:52,920
- (chuckles) Yep, my
sister turned into

709
00:53:52,920 --> 00:53:53,880
quite a little snob.

710
00:53:55,400 --> 00:53:57,600
- She liked the scene
every once in a while.

711
00:54:00,200 --> 00:54:02,160
I know she was happiest
when she would have a book,

712
00:54:02,160 --> 00:54:04,960
curled up by the fire
at the lake house.

713
00:54:11,040 --> 00:54:11,920
I miss her.

714
00:54:14,400 --> 00:54:15,960
- Yeah, me too.

715
00:54:26,720 --> 00:54:28,280
Say, Bobby.

716
00:54:29,240 --> 00:54:30,280
Susan and I were talking.

717
00:54:32,040 --> 00:54:34,160
We'd love to have little
Gregory come stay with us,

718
00:54:34,160 --> 00:54:35,720
you know, for a little while,

719
00:54:35,720 --> 00:54:38,280
just till you get like, you
know, a little sturdier.

720
00:54:41,240 --> 00:54:43,440
Yeah, my mom can't
look after him forever.

721
00:54:43,440 --> 00:54:45,280
She's getting old

722
00:54:45,280 --> 00:54:48,120
and it'll be really
good training wheels
for us, you know.

723
00:54:48,120 --> 00:54:49,760
Having a kid of our own.

724
00:54:49,760 --> 00:54:51,360
It's all Susan talks about.

725
00:54:52,840 --> 00:54:55,640
You know, the doctor
said kinda tick tock, so.

726
00:54:58,920 --> 00:55:00,520
- You really think
that's a good idea?

727
00:55:00,520 --> 00:55:01,280
- My mom does.

728
00:55:02,520 --> 00:55:04,080
- I know what Barbara
thinks about it.

729
00:55:04,080 --> 00:55:06,320
- Yeah, but like, you know,
Susan and I discussed it

730
00:55:06,320 --> 00:55:09,200
with her and, you
know, we all agree

731
00:55:09,200 --> 00:55:10,840
it's probably for the best.

732
00:55:12,160 --> 00:55:14,840
Obviously we need, you
know, your go ahead, but.

733
00:55:14,840 --> 00:55:16,440
- Really?
- Yeah, really.

734
00:55:18,040 --> 00:55:21,000
- What about your
work and daycare?

735
00:55:23,080 --> 00:55:26,160
- Susan's actually
leaving her job,

736
00:55:26,160 --> 00:55:29,080
so she can watch
Gregory full time.

737
00:55:31,920 --> 00:55:32,680
- Well.

738
00:55:35,000 --> 00:55:36,520
Let me think about it.
- Yeah.

739
00:55:42,080 --> 00:55:43,040
- I don't know, man.

740
00:55:44,280 --> 00:55:45,360
I'll have to check
with Bridgette.

741
00:55:47,000 --> 00:55:49,480
- Well, you know, think it over.

742
00:55:49,480 --> 00:55:50,800
Take all the time you need.

743
00:55:52,840 --> 00:55:55,360
- Have you all
decided what you want?

744
00:55:55,360 --> 00:55:57,360
- I will have a cheeseburger,

745
00:55:57,360 --> 00:56:01,680
but instead of french
fries, I will have coleslaw.

746
00:56:01,680 --> 00:56:04,800
- Order never changes,
ever since we were kids.

747
00:56:04,800 --> 00:56:05,520
- And you?

748
00:56:06,840 --> 00:56:08,160
- I always get the same thing,

749
00:56:08,160 --> 00:56:12,280
but today I think I
want the meatloaf.

750
00:56:12,280 --> 00:56:15,240
But instead of french fries,
can I have a baked potato?

751
00:56:15,240 --> 00:56:16,040
- [Waitress] Okay.

752
00:56:16,040 --> 00:56:16,840
- Ooh!

753
00:56:16,840 --> 00:56:17,960
- And to drink?

754
00:56:17,960 --> 00:56:19,480
- Yeah, I'll have a Dos Equis.

755
00:56:21,160 --> 00:56:22,200
- Me, too.

756
00:56:22,200 --> 00:56:23,960
- Okay, sounds good.

757
00:56:23,960 --> 00:56:25,200
I'll get your order in

758
00:56:25,200 --> 00:56:26,320
and I'll be right
back with your beers.

759
00:56:26,320 --> 00:56:27,080
- Thank you.

760
00:56:30,400 --> 00:56:31,640
I swear she hasn't changed.

761
00:56:34,640 --> 00:56:36,160
- Rachel or.

762
00:56:37,560 --> 00:56:40,640
I don't know, I didn't
see her name tag.

763
00:56:40,640 --> 00:56:41,400
'Night.

764
00:56:52,160 --> 00:56:53,120
Bridgette?

765
00:56:54,160 --> 00:56:54,920
Are you here?

766
00:56:57,760 --> 00:57:00,120
(eerie music)

767
00:57:02,480 --> 00:57:03,200
Oh my God!

768
00:57:04,360 --> 00:57:05,600
Bridgette, what are you doing?

769
00:57:05,600 --> 00:57:07,840
Why are you like this,
what's happening?

770
00:57:07,840 --> 00:57:09,160
- Why are you giving
our son away, Bobby?

771
00:57:09,160 --> 00:57:10,640
- What?

772
00:57:10,640 --> 00:57:11,880
What?

773
00:57:11,880 --> 00:57:13,160
What are you, what
are you talking about?

774
00:57:13,160 --> 00:57:15,280
- Can't you see what
they're trying to do?

775
00:57:15,280 --> 00:57:16,360
They can't have a
child of their own,

776
00:57:16,360 --> 00:57:17,640
so they're trying to take ours.

777
00:57:17,640 --> 00:57:19,240
- No, Bridgette,
it's not like that.

778
00:57:19,240 --> 00:57:20,840
- Then tell me what it is like.

779
00:57:22,200 --> 00:57:23,600
I'm curious to hear
how you think this is

780
00:57:23,600 --> 00:57:24,640
gonna play itself out.

781
00:57:24,640 --> 00:57:25,920
- Oh, gosh.

782
00:57:25,920 --> 00:57:27,840
You're so cold, let
me get you a blanket.

783
00:57:35,160 --> 00:57:36,680
It's cold in here, Bridgette!

784
00:57:37,760 --> 00:57:38,480
Thanks a lot!

785
00:57:56,920 --> 00:57:59,160
(screeching)

786
00:57:59,160 --> 00:58:00,120
Bridgette!

787
00:58:01,120 --> 00:58:02,120
What are you doing?

788
00:58:02,120 --> 00:58:03,680
You're scaring me!

789
00:58:03,680 --> 00:58:05,160
What are you doing out there?

790
00:58:05,160 --> 00:58:07,440
(crashing)

791
00:58:17,120 --> 00:58:18,360
Bridgette what are...

792
00:58:28,080 --> 00:58:30,640
(lock clicking)

793
00:58:33,000 --> 00:58:33,760
Oh.

794
00:58:35,560 --> 00:58:36,920
What am I doing?

795
00:58:43,880 --> 00:58:46,360
(line ringing)

796
00:58:49,280 --> 00:58:51,080
- [Andrew] Hey,
you've reached Andrew.

797
00:58:51,080 --> 00:58:53,520
- Ah.
(ragged breathing)

798
00:58:53,520 --> 00:58:54,920
I...

799
00:58:54,920 --> 00:58:55,720
Andrew?

800
00:58:55,720 --> 00:58:56,480
Hey, it's me.

801
00:58:58,640 --> 00:59:01,520
Yeah, I just wanted to call and
say thanks again for dinner.

802
00:59:03,120 --> 00:59:05,400
And (stammering)
I'm not seeing...

803
00:59:07,240 --> 00:59:08,200
I just...

804
00:59:09,560 --> 00:59:12,520
I'm not feeling too well and
I could use a little company.

805
00:59:13,920 --> 00:59:15,160
I don't know if,

806
00:59:15,160 --> 00:59:16,880
no, I guess I
didn't mention that.

807
00:59:16,880 --> 00:59:19,280
I guess I was too busy
(whispering quietly) myself.

808
00:59:19,280 --> 00:59:20,560
Sorry, sorry.

809
00:59:20,560 --> 00:59:22,080
Sorry, this is a
rambling message.

810
00:59:22,080 --> 00:59:23,120
I just...

811
00:59:23,120 --> 00:59:25,200
Yeah, give me a call
back when you get this.

812
00:59:25,200 --> 00:59:28,640
And we can talk and maybe I'll
be a little more coherent.

813
00:59:30,200 --> 00:59:34,000
You just, you know, like...
(screeching)

814
00:59:40,080 --> 00:59:42,720
(unlocking door)

815
00:59:51,800 --> 00:59:52,720
- Maggie, you home?

816
00:59:53,920 --> 00:59:54,920
Can I come over?

817
00:59:55,760 --> 00:59:58,320
(Muzak playing)

818
00:59:59,440 --> 01:00:01,600
(sighing)

819
01:00:19,200 --> 01:00:22,120
Maggie!
(knocking)

820
01:00:22,120 --> 01:00:23,960
Oh, Maggie!
(knocking)

821
01:00:23,960 --> 01:00:26,640
Maggie, sorry to bother you,
but I saw your light on,

822
01:00:26,640 --> 01:00:28,320
so I came over.

823
01:00:28,320 --> 01:00:33,160
(stammering) I'm not
feeling too well.

824
01:00:43,400 --> 01:00:44,200
- Hello.

825
01:00:44,200 --> 01:00:45,480
- Hey.

826
01:00:45,480 --> 01:00:49,280
- Can I get this and
a bottle of Old Monk?

827
01:00:49,280 --> 01:00:51,480
- Oh, sorry, all sold out.

828
01:00:51,480 --> 01:00:53,040
- Sold out?

829
01:00:53,040 --> 01:00:55,320
- Yeah, my wife delivered the
last case of it yesterday.

830
01:00:57,600 --> 01:00:59,240
- Oh, shit.

831
01:00:59,240 --> 01:01:04,040
I tied you up.

832
01:01:09,840 --> 01:01:11,640
- Must be some kinda
bachelorette party

833
01:01:11,640 --> 01:01:13,160
or something going
on up at the lake.

834
01:01:13,160 --> 01:01:14,480
- What?

835
01:01:14,480 --> 01:01:15,800
- Yeah, I've never sold
so much of the stuff.

836
01:01:15,800 --> 01:01:18,400
Next case won't be
in until next month.

837
01:01:18,400 --> 01:01:19,320
I have other rums,
though, if you--

838
01:01:19,320 --> 01:01:20,240
- Hey, wait a minute, did you,

839
01:01:20,240 --> 01:01:21,200
Did you sell it to this guy?

840
01:01:24,120 --> 01:01:24,880
- No.

841
01:01:26,200 --> 01:01:27,160
To her.

842
01:01:28,600 --> 01:01:31,240
- Come on, Bridgette,
why are you doing this?

843
01:01:31,240 --> 01:01:32,280
I didn't do anything!

844
01:01:34,120 --> 01:01:35,800
Nothing is gonna
happen to Gregory!

845
01:01:35,800 --> 01:01:37,080
No one is gonna take him!

846
01:01:40,800 --> 01:01:43,200
I'm gonna have to walk back
home through the woods now!

847
01:01:43,200 --> 01:01:44,280
Is that what you want?

848
01:01:54,120 --> 01:01:55,800
- All right.

849
01:01:55,800 --> 01:01:57,520
You know, the Captain
Morgan is really a lot--

850
01:01:57,520 --> 01:01:58,800
- Nah.

851
01:02:02,000 --> 01:02:03,320
- You want your change?

852
01:02:03,320 --> 01:02:04,480
- [Andrew] No.

853
01:02:07,920 --> 01:02:09,200
- Random.

854
01:02:09,200 --> 01:02:11,960
(phone vibrating)

855
01:02:14,280 --> 01:02:16,880
(knocking on door)

856
01:02:16,880 --> 01:02:19,360
- Maggie.

857
01:02:19,360 --> 01:02:22,080
(phone vibrating)

858
01:02:24,400 --> 01:02:26,800
Oh, she must be out.

859
01:02:28,960 --> 01:02:31,720
(phone vibrating)

860
01:02:42,440 --> 01:02:44,800
(Bobby yawns)

861
01:02:46,920 --> 01:02:47,680
- Bobby!

862
01:02:48,760 --> 01:02:49,760
(knocking)

863
01:02:49,760 --> 01:02:50,840
Bobby, you here?

864
01:02:50,840 --> 01:02:51,800
Bobby!

865
01:03:03,280 --> 01:03:06,160
(mobile vibrating)

866
01:03:18,400 --> 01:03:19,120
Bobby?

867
01:03:20,360 --> 01:03:21,600
Bobby, are you out there?

868
01:03:24,080 --> 01:03:24,800
Bobby!

869
01:03:27,080 --> 01:03:27,840
Hey!

870
01:03:27,840 --> 01:03:28,800
Hey, Bobby!

871
01:03:31,040 --> 01:03:31,800
Get up, Bobby!

872
01:03:35,560 --> 01:03:36,600
I'm coming, Bob!

873
01:03:45,560 --> 01:03:47,160
(car door shutting)

874
01:03:47,160 --> 01:03:47,920
Hello?

875
01:03:51,840 --> 01:03:52,600
Hello?

876
01:03:56,960 --> 01:03:57,760
Bobby?

877
01:03:57,760 --> 01:03:58,720
Hey!

878
01:03:59,800 --> 01:04:01,120
Bobby!

879
01:04:01,120 --> 01:04:02,000
Bobby, wake up!

880
01:04:02,000 --> 01:04:02,800
- What?

881
01:04:02,800 --> 01:04:03,840
What?

882
01:04:03,840 --> 01:04:04,720
Wait, what's going on?

883
01:04:04,720 --> 01:04:05,680
Where...

884
01:04:06,960 --> 01:04:07,720
Where am I?

885
01:04:08,920 --> 01:04:10,960
- You're at a cabin
across the lake.

886
01:04:13,760 --> 01:04:14,720
- It's cold.

887
01:04:17,680 --> 01:04:18,440
Oh.

888
01:04:19,640 --> 01:04:21,760
Oh, Bridgette took my boat.

889
01:04:23,240 --> 01:04:26,160
- Bridgette did not
take your boat, Bobby.

890
01:04:26,160 --> 01:04:27,080
You're in shock.

891
01:04:27,080 --> 01:04:28,760
What are you doing over here?

892
01:04:28,760 --> 01:04:32,400
- Miss Maggie's light was
on and I came over to...

893
01:04:33,800 --> 01:04:36,560
I didn't want to be alone, I
should've asked you to stay.

894
01:04:36,560 --> 01:04:37,360
- What?

895
01:04:37,360 --> 01:04:38,160
Who is Maggie?

896
01:04:38,160 --> 01:04:38,920
- Mrs. Moss.

897
01:04:39,800 --> 01:04:41,320
This is her house.

898
01:04:41,320 --> 01:04:43,320
She remembers you from
when you were a little kid.

899
01:04:43,320 --> 01:04:46,240
- Dude, the Mosses haven't
been up here in years.

900
01:04:46,240 --> 01:04:47,760
- No, I had lunch here.

901
01:04:50,240 --> 01:04:51,800
I had soup.

902
01:04:51,800 --> 01:04:53,520
- Soup?

903
01:04:53,520 --> 01:04:54,880
How many pills have you taken?

904
01:04:57,440 --> 01:04:58,200
- Some.

905
01:04:59,680 --> 01:05:00,920
- Have you been drinking?
- No.

906
01:05:00,920 --> 01:05:02,720
- Don't lie to me, Bobby.
- No.

907
01:05:02,720 --> 01:05:04,040
- I went to the liquor store.

908
01:05:04,040 --> 01:05:05,560
- No, no, no, no, I didn't
drink those, I just.

909
01:05:05,560 --> 01:05:07,400
I wanted to hear
what they had to say.

910
01:05:08,600 --> 01:05:10,000
They don't talk
unless they're full.

911
01:05:11,800 --> 01:05:12,880
- Okay, let's,

912
01:05:12,880 --> 01:05:13,680
let's get you to
the hospital, man.

913
01:05:13,680 --> 01:05:15,040
Can you stand?

914
01:05:15,040 --> 01:05:16,200
- Of course I can stand.

915
01:05:21,040 --> 01:05:22,120
Wait.

916
01:05:22,120 --> 01:05:22,920
- Hey.

917
01:05:22,920 --> 01:05:23,680
- No, Maggie.

918
01:05:27,280 --> 01:05:28,640
Maggie Was here.

919
01:05:31,160 --> 01:05:32,760
She was in there.

920
01:05:32,760 --> 01:05:35,440
- Look, man, we can talk
about it later, all right?

921
01:05:35,440 --> 01:05:37,560
Let's just, let's get
you to the hospital.

922
01:05:37,560 --> 01:05:39,240
- No, I'm not,
don't take me there.

923
01:05:39,240 --> 01:05:41,080
- Bobby, I need to have
a doctor look at you.

924
01:05:41,080 --> 01:05:42,400
I don't know why
you're hallucinating.

925
01:05:42,400 --> 01:05:43,920
- Don't take me there.

926
01:05:43,920 --> 01:05:45,120
They let Bridgette die.

927
01:05:46,240 --> 01:05:48,520
- They didn't let Bridgette die.

928
01:05:48,520 --> 01:05:49,960
It was an accident, man.

929
01:05:49,960 --> 01:05:52,560
It was an accident.

930
01:05:52,560 --> 01:05:54,920
- I shoulda been the one
driving, it shoulda been me.

931
01:05:54,920 --> 01:05:56,680
- That's not how
it went, all right?

932
01:05:56,680 --> 01:05:57,840
It's just, it's not.

933
01:05:58,960 --> 01:05:59,720
Okay?

934
01:06:01,680 --> 01:06:03,640
Let's get you to a hospital.

935
01:06:03,640 --> 01:06:06,280
- No.

936
01:06:06,280 --> 01:06:07,480
Take me to the cabin.

937
01:06:07,480 --> 01:06:08,920
Take me to the
cabin, I'll warm up.

938
01:06:10,320 --> 01:06:14,880
I'll be fine.

939
01:06:14,880 --> 01:06:16,360
- All right.

940
01:06:16,360 --> 01:06:18,600
Just, let's get in the car.

941
01:06:44,960 --> 01:06:47,800
(loud banging)

942
01:06:47,800 --> 01:06:48,560
Bobby!

943
01:06:50,680 --> 01:06:52,760
- Whoa, how did that get here?

944
01:06:52,760 --> 01:06:54,360
Wait, that's weird.

945
01:06:54,360 --> 01:06:55,560
She brought the boat back.

946
01:06:55,560 --> 01:06:56,320
- Who?

947
01:06:56,320 --> 01:06:57,640
- Bridgette.

948
01:06:57,640 --> 01:07:00,040
- Robert, Bridgette did
not bring the boat back!

949
01:07:00,040 --> 01:07:01,800
- No, when I came down
here earlier to go home,

950
01:07:01,800 --> 01:07:03,040
she was sitting on it in
the middle of the lake

951
01:07:03,040 --> 01:07:04,760
and she was really angry at me!

952
01:07:04,760 --> 01:07:05,960
- What was she angry about?

953
01:07:05,960 --> 01:07:07,320
- She thought I was
giving away Gregory

954
01:07:07,320 --> 01:07:08,560
to you and Susan.

955
01:07:08,560 --> 01:07:10,320
- Dude, this is
getting ridiculous!

956
01:07:10,320 --> 01:07:11,680
What are you doing?

957
01:07:11,680 --> 01:07:13,000
- I'm going to tie the boat up.

958
01:07:16,280 --> 01:07:17,120
- What?

959
01:07:17,120 --> 01:07:18,480
What is that stuff?

960
01:07:18,480 --> 01:07:19,480
Come on, Bobby.

961
01:07:19,480 --> 01:07:20,640
We're gonna go, all right?

962
01:07:20,640 --> 01:07:22,080
I'm thinking you
didn't tie the boat up,

963
01:07:22,080 --> 01:07:23,000
we'll grab it in the morning.

964
01:07:23,000 --> 01:07:24,320
We gotta get you warm.

965
01:07:24,320 --> 01:07:25,640
- I threw all that
stuff in the lake!

966
01:07:25,640 --> 01:07:27,640
- Bobby, I don't know
what you think you--

967
01:07:27,640 --> 01:07:28,760
- Look, did you see that?

968
01:07:28,760 --> 01:07:29,960
- What?

969
01:07:29,960 --> 01:07:30,720
- The curtain just
moved in Maggie's house,

970
01:07:30,720 --> 01:07:31,960
she's gotta be home now.

971
01:07:31,960 --> 01:07:34,760
- Bobby, no one has
been there in 10 years!

972
01:07:34,760 --> 01:07:36,200
Why can't you see that?

973
01:07:36,200 --> 01:07:36,960
I told you.

974
01:07:41,040 --> 01:07:42,600
This is a bad idea!

975
01:07:42,600 --> 01:07:45,480
Look, that is a very,
very bad idea, man.

976
01:07:45,480 --> 01:07:46,760
We've had enough
drama for one night,

977
01:07:46,760 --> 01:07:47,840
let's go home.

978
01:07:47,840 --> 01:07:48,800
- No, I have to see.

979
01:07:51,640 --> 01:07:52,440
I was here.

980
01:07:52,440 --> 01:07:54,760
This was so real.

981
01:07:56,160 --> 01:07:57,920
- Bobby, I will bring you
back first thing tomorrow

982
01:07:57,920 --> 01:08:00,280
and you can look around
to your heart's content

983
01:08:00,280 --> 01:08:01,720
in the daytime, okay?

984
01:08:04,520 --> 01:08:05,440
Come on.

985
01:08:05,440 --> 01:08:07,480
- What is happening to me?

986
01:08:39,880 --> 01:08:40,800
Is this a dream?

987
01:08:40,800 --> 01:08:41,680
Is this just a bad dream?

988
01:08:42,640 --> 01:08:43,400
- What?

989
01:08:45,040 --> 01:08:46,800
What are you talking about?

990
01:08:46,800 --> 01:08:47,560
- This.

991
01:08:48,840 --> 01:08:50,840
I can't tell what's real
and what's fake anymore.

992
01:08:51,720 --> 01:08:54,040
- This is real, Bobby.

993
01:08:54,040 --> 01:08:54,840
Okay?

994
01:08:54,840 --> 01:08:56,520
All this is real.

995
01:08:58,280 --> 01:09:01,080
Look, man, I think you've
suffered a traumatic experience

996
01:09:01,080 --> 01:09:04,800
and it's making you hear
things and see things

997
01:09:06,320 --> 01:09:09,360
and believe things
that don't exist, okay?

998
01:09:10,640 --> 01:09:12,920
And you couple that with
a lot of self medication

999
01:09:12,920 --> 01:09:14,400
and voila!

1000
01:09:14,400 --> 01:09:15,640
- Psychotic break?

1001
01:09:15,640 --> 01:09:17,800
- Hey, I don't know what
they'd call it, but.

1002
01:09:20,120 --> 01:09:21,800
- I know.

1003
01:09:21,800 --> 01:09:23,080
- Bobby.

1004
01:09:23,080 --> 01:09:24,680
I'm not judging you, all right?

1005
01:09:25,720 --> 01:09:27,000
I have no idea what
you're going through,

1006
01:09:27,000 --> 01:09:28,720
losing the love of
your life like that,

1007
01:09:30,880 --> 01:09:33,440
but she was my
little sister, okay?

1008
01:09:33,440 --> 01:09:36,560
It's been tough on all of us.

1009
01:09:36,560 --> 01:09:37,680
Especially you and my mom.

1010
01:09:39,440 --> 01:09:40,400
- Barbara was right.

1011
01:09:43,080 --> 01:09:46,320
It should've been
me, it would've been
easier if I'd died.

1012
01:09:46,320 --> 01:09:48,480
I just, I don't
know if I can go on.

1013
01:09:48,480 --> 01:09:50,000
Bridgette was so much stronger.

1014
01:09:50,000 --> 01:09:50,800
I just, I can't.

1015
01:09:52,880 --> 01:09:54,480
- Bobby.

1016
01:09:54,480 --> 01:09:57,880
Hey, let's get you inside, man.

1017
01:09:57,880 --> 01:09:58,840
Okay?

1018
01:10:00,800 --> 01:10:01,760
- Okay.

1019
01:10:09,720 --> 01:10:12,480
- Cool?
- And Andrew, don't leave me.

1020
01:10:12,480 --> 01:10:14,480
Don't leave me even
for a second, okay?

1021
01:10:14,480 --> 01:10:15,800
- Okay.

1022
01:10:15,800 --> 01:10:17,480
- That's when she comes,
that's when she comes for me.

1023
01:10:17,480 --> 01:10:18,760
- Look, I won't, man, all right?

1024
01:10:18,760 --> 01:10:20,600
- And I'm the only
one who can see her.

1025
01:10:21,920 --> 01:10:23,360
Her and General Washington.

1026
01:10:24,760 --> 01:10:25,720
- What?

1027
01:10:28,640 --> 01:10:30,840
- I sometimes see
General Washington, too,

1028
01:10:30,840 --> 01:10:32,640
in the lake and in the woods.

1029
01:10:34,360 --> 01:10:36,160
I thought it was
reenactors at first,

1030
01:10:36,160 --> 01:10:37,880
but now I'm not so sure.

1031
01:10:37,880 --> 01:10:39,840
- Oh, boy.

1032
01:10:42,200 --> 01:10:43,760
Okay, yeah.

1033
01:10:43,760 --> 01:10:45,800
Let's go inside.

1034
01:10:52,600 --> 01:10:53,960
Classic.

1035
01:10:53,960 --> 01:10:55,320
Well, at least the car started.

1036
01:10:55,320 --> 01:10:57,720
- Oh, the light's
been flickering.

1037
01:10:59,120 --> 01:11:00,080
Something must be loose.

1038
01:11:00,080 --> 01:11:01,920
I keep meaning to check it out.

1039
01:11:01,920 --> 01:11:02,680
- You should.

1040
01:11:04,720 --> 01:11:06,320
I'm just gonna
start a fire, man.

1041
01:11:06,320 --> 01:11:07,280
- All right.

1042
01:11:09,280 --> 01:11:10,840
- Hey, get over here, man.

1043
01:11:10,840 --> 01:11:12,800
Warm up now.

1044
01:11:17,800 --> 01:11:19,080
I'm gonna get you
a blanket, too.

1045
01:11:19,880 --> 01:11:21,720
- Oh, that sounds nice.

1046
01:11:21,720 --> 01:11:22,680
Oh, and a shot, too.

1047
01:11:24,720 --> 01:11:25,800
- Okay.

1048
01:11:25,800 --> 01:11:27,520
Just this once.

1049
01:11:27,520 --> 01:11:28,720
I'm gonna have one, too.

1050
01:11:31,760 --> 01:11:32,960
- Oh, wait, I'll get it!

1051
01:11:34,200 --> 01:11:34,960
- [Andrew] Robert.

1052
01:11:36,000 --> 01:11:37,520
- I can explain that.
- Can you?

1053
01:11:38,840 --> 01:11:39,920
- They just showed up.

1054
01:11:41,680 --> 01:11:42,520
They're very wise.

1055
01:11:44,080 --> 01:11:47,080
- Yeah, that's not really
a great explanation, Bobby.

1056
01:11:47,080 --> 01:11:48,200
- They're all I've got.

1057
01:11:49,680 --> 01:11:51,400
- Dude, you named them?

1058
01:11:51,400 --> 01:11:52,240
- They have names.

1059
01:11:53,520 --> 01:11:54,920
They'll tell you, if you listen.

1060
01:11:57,880 --> 01:12:01,040
(eerie music)

1061
01:12:01,040 --> 01:12:04,480
It's her.

1062
01:12:04,480 --> 01:12:05,680
She was just there, I swear!

1063
01:12:05,680 --> 01:12:07,960
- You gotta stop doing
this to yourself, man.

1064
01:12:09,520 --> 01:12:10,360
Bridgette is gone.

1065
01:12:12,280 --> 01:12:13,880
- It was so real.

1066
01:12:13,880 --> 01:12:16,280
- Tomorrow morning I am
taking you to a doctor.

1067
01:12:16,280 --> 01:12:18,480
If you don't wanna go
to the hospital up here,

1068
01:12:18,480 --> 01:12:20,560
I'll take you to one
in the city, but.

1069
01:12:20,560 --> 01:12:22,240
- Andrew?
- Yes?

1070
01:12:22,240 --> 01:12:23,160
- I'm scared, man.

1071
01:12:24,720 --> 01:12:26,400
I don't think I'm gonna
make it through the night.

1072
01:12:26,400 --> 01:12:28,320
- Of course you are.

1073
01:12:28,320 --> 01:12:30,840
- No, I got a bad
feeling about this night.

1074
01:12:30,840 --> 01:12:33,880
- Bobby, I will stay up
the entire night with you.

1075
01:12:33,880 --> 01:12:35,400
- I don't think you can stop it.

1076
01:12:37,000 --> 01:12:37,920
- What are you saying?

1077
01:12:37,920 --> 01:12:39,560
- I don't know, I don't know.

1078
01:12:39,560 --> 01:12:41,400
It's gonna be a long night.

1079
01:12:41,400 --> 01:12:42,520
- Uh-huh.

1080
01:12:42,520 --> 01:12:45,080
- People can die of
fright, can't they?

1081
01:12:45,080 --> 01:12:47,520
(loud banging)

1082
01:12:49,600 --> 01:12:53,520
- Okay, that is weird.

1083
01:12:55,600 --> 01:12:56,360
- See?

